<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Taking a break from my iksar shaman, I have been playing my shadowknight on Vallon and am the level I spend my time in Highkeep and I'm encountering many shaman that don't seem to understand the strengths of shaman.  In particular--meleeing is not a shaman strength.<P>At level 20, the shaman has a weapon skill of 84 maxed.  This is equal to a level 16 warrior.  Yet the shaman at this time does not have double attack and all melees and hybrids do at this point.  So imagine a shaman is fighting a level 20 creature.  He'd be effectively meleeing like he is fighting a red con.  He will never hit nearly 60% of the time or do the damage per second on his weapon.  In short, you'll be lucky to do a quarter of the damage of a warrior.  <P>At level 30, the shaman has a weapon skill of 124.  Now he melees like a level 24 warrior (without double attack of course).  On blue cons he will hit like a warrior against red or near red cons.  <P>The point of this is, shaman are not good at melee.  Bards at least have the same weapon skill as warriors (without double attack again) and no one is impressed with their melee damage.  Double attack is one big difference between the tanks and the shaman; weapon cap is the second big difference.  <BR>A shaman can melee as well as a druid, and we are all aware how druids should not be meleeing.<P>By level 24, I think shaman should be meleeing under these situations.  <BR>1) Soloing.<BR>2) To keep skills maxed for soloing later.<BR>3) When at full mana.<BR>4) In between refreshes of cannibalize.<BR>5) Easy exp camps where you have no chance of dying.  <BR>6) Partnering with rogues.<P>At other times, the shaman should be medding, casting, or canni dancing, and will not perform at his full potential by meleeing, and may be hurting the group.  Please realize that shaman are not good at melee.  They are not warrior-priests.  You can't taunt someone off another through melee.  An easy lesson, but so many shaman think it is worthwhile to melee in groups.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
