Well, I agree with you in part. It all depends on the group make up as to what the shaman should be doing. In general, the shaman will need to be meditating and canni-dancing through all fights. That is if he is able to sit down for the agro he has gained. If he is full mana and able to melee, then you are pulling to slow for the group.<P>I know I have been main tank for a couple rather unusual groups but that just shows the versatility of the class. Being able to tank does not mean we are a great melee'r. I can get taunt from most any tank for a brief period of time.<P>--------------------<P>~I'm a little teapot, short and stout. Here is my handle. Here is my spout. Tip me over and pour me out.~ Ancient Halfling Warrior Chant<P>Failbhean, 51 Champion<BR>Failbhe, 52 Mystic
