<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree, with the exception that meleeing solo to work up skills to later solo is forgetting to mention something.<P>Defense and natural AC are built up by meleeing with mobs too, so that effects you enormously later even for groups.  I'd say its group effect is probably even more significant than its solo effect.<P>On meleeing in groups, personally, if I'm grouped, I'm usually cannibalizing all through a fight.  If I have full mana, I slap a chloro or regrowth on somebody, or a DOT on the mob before I melee.  I can regen mana faster than a cleric, so sometimes I slap a heal on too even if we have a cleric.  Melee is really the least I can contribute, so I contribute it least.<P>The only exception to this is if a mob is running away and we don't want it to get to its friends and start a train, or if it's a gating mob or a situation like that where the stun from my howling harpoon would make a major difference from the stun alone, not the melee damage.
</FONT>
