<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Methinks that you may be missing the point of Shaman melee: Dont think of it as "Shaman melee-ing mobs", think of it a s "mobs melee-ing Shaman" <P>Tis not about dealing significant damage to a mob: That mob has lots and lots of hit points and you are not hitting for very many. The whole point of Shaman melee is that we have quite a lot of hit points and potentially very high armor class. So, if a mob is melee-ing you, it is probaly not melee-ing some poor pyjama wearing caster who only has double figure hitpoints and even less armor class.<P>In a group situation, if we get an "add" or respawn "pop" that aggros a caster I will always try to get the mob to aggro onto me so that I can keep the mob occupied until the tanks are not too busy to kill it for me. I engage it knowing that I am unable to melee it to death, but knowing that I can melee it long after it would have killed all the other casters
</FONT>
