<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Druids and clerics are also limited to weapons that have relatively terrible damage dealing ratios.<P>There are plenty of shamans who do decent damage with 2hb's and great ratio piercers.  Also, many of the shaman weapons have DD/dot procs as well.<P>Try not to think of it as "shamans shouldnt be meleeing at all because they cant do it like a monk."  This approach really isnt a great angle.  Why not then say that we also shouldnt bother with a pet because we cant do it like a magician?<P>The ability to dish out decent damage in melee is just aspect of a shamans versatility.  Dealing damage and tanking are two completely different tasks however (consider also that a warrior, who is the best tank, does not deal the most damage in melee)<P>At level 44, decked out in +str/dex gear (sacraficing TONS of ac for this), fully buffed (barb shammy with 200str/190dex) with a spine chill spear (10/28, 3sta, 6wis, eff:shock of ice - ~35pt dd) I would estimate I usually deal out about 50-60% the damage that a warrior is doing.  Granted, I only attack in melee when I either a) have a chanter in the group or b) am not the primary healer.<P>I wouldnt compare classes based on skill maxes alone because gear makes a HUGE difference for melee classes.
