I disagree Jaiden.  My high char is a rogue and when I compare the damage I do as a shaman, it's pretty pathetic.  When I compare the rate of attack, it's also pathetic.  As a midlevel shaman I use a slime coated harpoon, an excellent 10/25 weapon, but I can't ever hope to hit 50% of the time on a blue mob.  Strength makes up for lack of skill to a certain extent, but you can't match up a warrior with the same strength at level 30, and he will do at least three or four times the damage.  <P>Shaman lack: double attack (up to 50% more damage assuming the same weapon skill), dual wield (an extra 33% damage assuming same weap skill), and an extra melee attack (i.e., kick or slam, an extra 30 damage per min), a chance to critical, and have to wait till 40 before they actually get a strength bonuses on damage.  Casting spells also resets the timer on our attack.  The lower weapon skill is the most significant part disadvantage however.  A level 24 warrior (who never trained double attack or dual wield, and who never kicks or bashes) attacking a level 28 mob will have a dramatically different damage histogram than a level 30 warrior on the same level 28 mob.  <P>With a slime coated harpoon, my shaman might be lucky to get 150 damage a min on a blue mob.  A level 30 warrior by comparison, would do over 400 damage per minute not counting criticals using a slime coated harpoon and a crystallized long sword.<P>Remember, shaman use the same weapon formula (4 x level + 4) as intelligence casters.  It's that bad.  I suspect a shaman will be better at stopping a runner by medding for one or two ticks and nuking, than standing up to melee.<P>Here's another point.  At level 30 druids can probably do the same damage as shaman:  they get attack bonuses from flame fist, strength of earth and wolf form that probably match up evenly with the shaman's high strength.  A twink can wield a weapon just as good as anything shaman have, the dark ember.  Should a druid be meleeing instead of medding when they go out of mana and the tanks are sweating over a mob?  No.<BR>I know shaman have better AC than druids, but if the shaman is not getting into melee to tank, but just going into melee on the assumption he is acting effectively, more effective than slowing, doting, DDing, cannying, medding or healing, he is wrong.
</FONT>
