Ok, seeing as how there appears to be a few "cookie cutter" shamans posting to this thread, please let me clarify that...wait for it...<P>SHAMANS ARENT DRUIDS<P>Shamans are the hybrid of casters.  We arent as offensively spell oriented as the pure casters (int, druid, cleric if soloing specs) and arent as melee oriented as pure melees (all the rest)<P>Lisboa, musiceu, if you had bothered to read my post, I said that I meleed when I had a chanter in the group or am not primary healer.  I DID NOT say that I neglect my grouping responsibilities as a shaman to go poke some mob with my stick (oddly enuf...which works much better from the rear).  When I melee, I still slow and cripple, regen myself and tank, buff and haste (usually dont need to when meleeing cause chanter is along).  The difference is that instead of just sitting on my ass medding for one of our inefficient nukes or a dot that wont ever fully run its course, I use my offensive capabilities just about as inefficiently by meleeing.<P>Now please dont try to say something like "you should sit and nuke or dot or something", this is one of the reasons I mentioned the cookie cutter shaman.<P>Personally...I LIKE to poke the mob in the pooper with my stick, and if its a problem for those that would rather waste 200 mana on 400 damage (with resists), by all means *do that with your own shaman*.<P>Lisboa, also I am speaking of pure offensive shaman melee.  In this situation, I cannot tank much better than a chanter, but I make sure that I dont need to at the time (full group of 6, cleric, chanter, 2 melees, (other), shaman).  If Im going to have to tank, I dont wear str/dex gear.<P>I see you mentioned a few pieces of equipment, but you missed the point.  I mentioned gear altering melees (and to a lesser extent shamans meleeing) because every character is going to be equipped differently.  Why even try to rationalize the suggestion of banning one classes activity when the upper percentage of that class probably comes close to or surpasses the lower end of another class.<P>In other words...some shamans might melee about as well as or even better than some melee characters.  What you need to take into account are the other abilities of each class, personal preferences of the player, and good god just getting out of the grind of things sometimes.<P>itneverstops, /agree.  When I ditch my spear and go crazy with blight (/curses blight should have barb spirit hammer grr) I hit 2/5 swings on average probably.  I usually hit for about 50-60ish, and proc VERY often.
