<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Most shaman are aware of how much of an effect strength has in combo.  It is usually that everyone overestimates how much it does.  So I suggest Jaidan, that you log an evening of meleeing (with misses in if you want to get your hit ratio) and come back with a damage per minute number.  Then compare it to your tank's DPM or Copeland's weapon analyzer.  <P>Blight has a 23/47 ratio, this is 9.7 dam/s... assuming a good damage curve.  (By comparison a runic carver does 10 dam/s and costs 250 pp.  A typical tank at level 44 will be yielding a mithril two hander or better, which does 13.6 dam/s.)  <P>With a blight you get 12.7 attacks per minute.  Hitting 40% of the time, you hit 5 times a minute.  By the very nature of being a shaman, your average hit is not going to be too high.  Let's be generous and say it is an average 40 damage per hit (yes, you say you usually hit for 50-60 but the low end band on your hits is higher than the upper band).  Right there, 200 dam/min.  <P>According to Copeland, a 44 warr with a mithril two hander does 660 dam/min, not including slam or kick or criticals.
</FONT>
