I melee when I solo and partner. <P>Meleeing, slime coated harpoon, I can do as much damage in 42 seconds as my best poison dot, venom. So 42 seconds I do about 400 damage, if I have my Yak war club, I do an additional 75 - 225 damage. <P>When partnering I am normally the tank, damage receiving tank, for rogues, rangers and monks. Why, my ac is higher.  I have to be in there so I might as well melee. <P>In a group setting it depends on the group and situation.  I can debuff mob and than melee while canniblizing at the same time.  Reasons on why I will melee and canniblizing:<BR>1)Meleeing and cannilblizing is more efficient than casting dot/dd and medding, in my opinion.  <BR>2)Enchanter or bard in group (if lucky, both) and I find I have an over abundance of mana, > 60%.<BR>3)Group very, very, very light on melee types.<P>Most often I don't melee in group settings however when I have the chance I jump in there. <P>Str and Str buffs - provide a small increase in damage to maximum damage hit.  At a glance it does not do much but overtime it is more mana efficient than our dots. (example - str buff ratio 1:10 while our dots 1:5 mana per damage).  However, I would not drop AC for Str for any reason.<P>--------------------<P>Greymyst<P>You all are just jealous because the voices only speak to me.
