<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree Shamans who aren't in a "role" as healer or some such can make use of their melee skills.  Am I the only one who has ever pulled a mob off the caster or even off of a warrior to give cleric time to heal him?  To pull off fighter I melee then cast DD spell, if the fighter hasn't been fighting this mob too long there is a good chance it will come after you.  Another use is to cast an AOE on mobs to pull the green ones off the fighters so that they can take down a big guy faster.<P>We aren't the best nukers or the best healers or the best fighters.  This means if you limit yourself to only one of these roles your party would be better of with a wizard, cleric or warrior respectively.  Be flexible based on situation.  Flexibility (along with SOW) is the hallmark of the Shaman.<P>By the way NO ONE who has ever played a druid and a shaman past level 16 would ever say they have the same melee ability.  Druid's low AC and hit points make them big fat targets.  Druids may have better melee stats than an INT caster but as the man said "Twice nothing is still nothing."  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Onpur Armorer of the North
