Blarg, i agree to your last conclusion. Im a shaman at lvl 47 (i blue bub from 48) and even with piercing and 2hb almost maxed, and offense/defence at 20-30 point from max i melee incredible bad, in comparison with casting a dot or even nuke. If you want to melee, create a new shaman and play the first 15 levels again, or create a melee'er. <P>In a group i never enter melee. If i want to peal a mob, i cast a nuke/dot/slow/root whatever...<P>When soloing, however, i will enter melee, but only when my pet is dying or if i need to take some damage. But its more like tanking, than damage output, because i will try to cast a spell, meanwhile. Normally root =) and then back up, and let pet do damage, while i cast a new dot.<P>Please shamans, druids, wizards, enchanters, magicians and especially clerics (!) dont melee....<P>Wow i hate when i group with a cleric and i see him entering melee... the first thing i ask i do is : /g mana, cleric_01 ? If he answers FM! then i ask him to cast hp-ac buffs on the tanks or whoever are in need, or heal. If he answer anything else than that, then i kindly ask him to med up, so he will be ready for a train or next pull.<P><BR>- Andr<P>--------------------<P>Tunare Server :<P><B>Sarcoma </B>48, Barbarian Shaman<BR><B>Rhabdos </B>21, Woodelf Ranger<BR><B>Rhabdomyo </B>15, Barb Rogue<BR><B>Kriger </B>10, Dwarf Warrior<BR><B>Rhandom </B>10, Human Monk<BR><B>Roever </B>10, High Elf Mage<BR><B>Sharcoma</B> 7, High Elf Cleric
