Ok I will pipe up to an uncaring world.<P>I have a level 60 Thief. By far the most deadly, high damaging <Meele> class in the game.<P>I also play Snoww. Level 55 Shaman. Snoww Meeles almost every fight in an exp group. The only times she doesnt meele is if she has to get mana back due to being low mana.<P>Others will say I am wasting the groups time. Others will say the meele is dumb, or not efficiant. <P>I will tell those others to kiss my blight weilding ass. I am told on a regular basis that I am one of the best shaman people have ever seen. I do it all. I tank, Heal, Pull, Buff, slow, control a pet, root park, nuke, dot, and constantly save peoples asses. <P>I may not do as much damage with meele as a thief. But I would like to see a thief control a 9 pull. <I can><P>A shaman isnt the best at anything but slowing. But not being the best at something doesnt mean we can't contribute. <P>I dont do as much damage in meele as a paladin but the nice thing about a Damage over time is that you CAST it and then are free to do meele damage while it ticks off. Combine that with a procs damage over time and a steady 40 to 80 point hit and our meele is nothing to scoff at.<P>If some stupid ass shaman tells me to sit down and stop meeleing I will laugh in his face. I have been the main Healer, main tank, main puller and Main damage dealer in groups of 1 person to 6 people. I may not do it as well as a specialist but I never see a specialist doing multiple roles in a group.<P>Or put it this way. With no real uber equipment I can solo, toe to toe 3 blue critters in Karnors at the same time. Lets see a caster shaman do that. <He will run out of mana a long time before I run out of HP/blight procs/JBB casts/Swinging damage. If he has a Spear of fate and I have one as well Me meeling just means it dies faster.<P>Having a high wisdom just increases your med time. The med rate is constant. Only the pool is larger with a high wisdom. If you are not going OOM with every pull, or Full mana with every pull then why have that large of a mana pool. You are only increasing your med time.<P>Yet when you are OOM you can always cannib a couple times and get more mana. When you are out of HP you are dead and looking for a res. What keeps you from losing HP? Armour class, regen rate, and smart playing.<P>I have been playing a tank shaman for almost 2 years. People say it can't be done. I do it every day and prove that the naysayers are wrong. Well I am still having fun. and Others are enjoying grouping with me so I must be doing something right.<P>Snoww Silverhammer   Bashy Shaman E marr 55th level
