While you seem to be right about the caster weap skill (I could've sworn my enchanter was going up 4 a level), shaman have an offensive cap that raises 4+ 4 x level, versus a melee's 5 + 5 x level.  As for the druid 175 cap, I'm referring to a druid at level 29 being equal to a shaman in melee ability.  I think druids can still wield those velium brawl sticks if they want too, the best 2hb weapons out there.  The problem is the damage cap is still 39 at level 29.  <P>If we could gather 4 or 5 shaman around level 40-44 on Bertoxx, I think I could prove a point about shaman melee damage.  I bet my rogue, armed with a 9/20 and 12/29 weapon, can outdamage and kill steal a group of 4 or 5 shaman who do nothing but melee, given that any buff they receive they give to me (to simulate group buffing).
