<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Sure you CAN melee in a group.<P>But I'll bet that in most situations in a full group or in multiple groups(and multiple-group fighting becomes pretty common in the later game) you could contribute more with your mana.<P>Like I mentioned in another post above, I view myself as a mana battery for other casters.  I cast regrowth on every tank in the vicinity if I can, if he's taking any real damage, and heal mobs so the druids can spend their mana on blasts and the clerics have more mana for when we really need it, or malo mobs so casters get their full damage.  Melee is nice, but it's not spectacular by any means when in a full group(s).  Regeneration and cannibalizing is definitely a spectacular shaman specialty, though, and I use it to the full.  That means I use it for the good of the mana(and therefore, contributions) of casters and healers, as well as myself.  Er, not to mention, the survival of the tanks and others.<P>I think, frankly, that that's looking at things from a little better perspective, not missing the forest for the trees, if you follow.  Just because we can do damage with melee doesn't mean we should, or that it's the best idea.  Even if it works.  That's not at all the criteria I'm using, and I don't think it's the important one at all.<P>What's important is not what's good enough, but what's best.<P>And whether you can move from a tactical view to a strategic overview.  <P>Anyone can more or less figure out tactics.  I think using your mana correctly and aggressively, especially when there is more than one group on your raid, can raise your play level to a strategic one, making your play level of a higher order.<P>Frankly, I think playing that way is more difficult, more challenging, and probably more useful to our groups.  <P>And it takes one out of any "tunnel vision" that might be making our contributions less than they really could be.<P>There are often too many chiefs and too few indians, but I think that you can contribute, even if nobody ever realizes you're doing it, at the level an officer contributes rather than remaining mere plodding cannon fodder if you stretch your limits a bit.<P>Our rate of mana return makes us special, but our melee doesn't.  I think it makes sense to go with our strengths, and try to play at a higher level.
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
